benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to bundle

covered: Valid Request: TC01, TC02, TC03, TC13, TC14, TC15, TC17, TC18, TC19, TC22, TC23, TC25 cover successful updates and state variations with valid payloads and edge cases.
Non-Existing Resource: TC05 covers 404 when the bundle does not exist.
Missing/Invalid Headers and Authorization: TC06 covers missing required header; TC10 covers unauthorized access.
Validation and Error Handling: TC04 (invalid bundleId), TC07 (malformed JSON), TC08 (missing request body), TC09 (extra/unsupported fields), TC12 (security input), TC16 (extra URL parameter).
Server/Integration/Error Handling: TC11 (service unavailable), TC20 (inconsistent data), TC21 (transient network failure).
Edge and Security Scenarios: TC12 (SQL injection), TC19 (regression with special characters).
Performance: TC17 (normal load) and TC18 (peak load).
State Variation: TC22 (no existing custom fields) and TC23 (update existing fields).
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling behavior not tested (e.g., 429 responses under load).
Caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control) and GET-side caching implications not tested, and no GET-after-PUT validation.
Explicit concurrency race-condition scenarios beyond general load tests (no targeted race-condition test).
403 Forbidden scenarios (authorization with insufficient privileges) not covered.
Duplicate submission/idempotency checks for repeated PUT requests not explicitly tested.
Content-Type handling beyond JSON payloads (e.g., 415 Unsupported Media Type) not tested.
Validation of data types inside CustomField properties beyond JSON structure not deeply covered (e.g., type mismatches).
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests to verify 429 responses under burst requests and proper throttling behavior.
Add caching tests that exercise GET-after-PUT to validate ETag/Cache-Control headers and 304 responses where applicable.
Add explicit race-condition tests to ensure no data corruption when multiple clients update the same bundle simultaneously.
Add 403 Forbidden scenarios to cover authorized-but-allowed-roles cases, ensuring proper error handling for insufficient permissions.
Add idempotency/duplicate-submission tests to confirm PUT is idempotent where relevant and handles repeated submissions gracefully.
Add tests for unsupported content types (415) and for content-type negotiation when payload is not JSON.
Add deeper payload validation tests for field-type mismatches and schema validation beyond structural JSON correctness.
